==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hieroglyphical
<hw>Hi`er*o*glyph"ic*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[L. <ets>hieroglyphicus</ets>, Gr. <?/; <grk>"iero`s</grk> sacred +
<grk>gly`fein</grk> to carve: cf. F.
<ets>hi⟦eacute⟧roglyphique</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Emblematic; expressive of some meaning by
characters, pictures, or figures; <as>as, <ex>hieroglyphic</ex> writing;
a <ex>hieroglyphic</ex> obelisk.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Pages no better than blanks to common minds, to his,
hieroglyphical of wisest secrets.</q> <rj><qau>Prof.
Wilson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Resembling hieroglyphics; not decipherable.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧An <xex>hieroglyphical</xex> scrawl.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Sir W.
Scott.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>of or pertaining to hieroglyphs.</def>
<wns>[wns=1]</wns>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hieroglyphically</ent>⟦br⟧
